Jenni Evans, News24Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa. (Denzil Maregele, Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - ANC deputy president Cyril Ramaphosa will hit the election campaign trail again on Monday, this time for by-elections to be held in George, the party said.Ramaphosa plans to start early with a walkabout and a meeting in Uniondale, then a spot of canvassing in Ward 11, Thembalethu, said Western Cape head of organising Richard Dyantyi.He will round off with a mini-rally in Ngcakani Street between 16:00 and 17:00.A seat in Ward 11 became vacant after the death of DA councillor Luxamile Xesi in a house fire last September.The by-election will be held on Wednesday, February 1.According to the Electoral Commission, the 4 227 registered voters can vote at Christ the Redeemer Church in Thembalethu, Gateway Lodge, the Lutheran Church in Rondevlei and at the Pine Lodge Resort.A by-election in Ward 25 would also be held after the death of ANC councillor Marlin Du Preez. He was found dead at home.The 3 859 registered voters in Ward 25 can vote at the Lyonville community hall, the Ezeljacht Primary School, Diepkloof Voorskool, Hartbeesriver Primary School and Bassou farms.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.